<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="40" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,564,951]" pageId="7" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,708,735]" pageId="7" pageNumber="40">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Forewing length is 11.5 mm in males. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Singh &amp; Kirti &amp; Datta &amp; Joshi &amp; Volynkin" authorityYear="2019" box="[777,1130,708,734]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Dolgoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rectoides" subSpecies="arunachala">
<emphasis box="[777,1130,708,734]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="40">Dolgoma rectoides arunachala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from the nominate subspecies by its slightly larger size. The male genitalia of the new subspecies (
<figureCitation box="[1216,1299,744,771]" captionStart="FIGURES 37–40" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1924,1949]" captionTargetBox="[154,1435,170,1896]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1435,166,1905]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 37–40. Dolgoma (37–39) and Teuloma (40) spp., male genitalia. 37, D. recta, paratype, Central Thailand, slide AV4734 Volynkin; 38, D. recta, NE India, prep. H. S. Datta; 39, D. rectoides arunachala, Holotype, NE India, prep. H. S. Datta; 40, T. oblitterans, Sri Lanka, slide NHMUK010315247 Volynkin (©NHMUK)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3474655" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3474655/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="40">Fig. 37</figureCitation>
) are similar to those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="rectoides Dubatolov" authorityYear="2012" box="[277,436,780,806]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Dolgoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rectoides" subSpecies="rectoides">
<emphasis box="[277,436,780,806]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="40">D. r. rectoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(illustrated by Dubatolov 2012), but differ by the narrower valva with the nearly straight ventral margin of sacculus (that is convex distally in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="rectoides Dubatolov" authorityYear="2012" box="[744,902,816,842]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Dolgoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rectoides" subSpecies="rectoides">
<emphasis box="[744,902,816,842]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="40">D. r. rectoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,564,951]" box="[199,426,852,878]" pageId="7" pageNumber="40">Female is unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
